  "informal_statement": "For every real x with x >= -1 and every natural number n, 1 + n*x <= (1 + x)^n (Bernoulli's inequality).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n. Base case n = 0: both sides equal 1. Successor case: from ih : 1 + n*x <= (1+x)^n and 1+x >= 0 (from x >= -1), multiply ih by (1+x) on the right (mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right) to get (1+n*x)*(1+x) <= (1+x)^n*(1+x) = (1+x)^(n+1). Expand the left side to 1 + (n+1)*x + n*x^2 and drop the nonnegative n*x^2 term (sq_nonneg x) to land on 1 + (n+1)*x; nlinarith closes the chain.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem bernoulli_inequality (n : ℕ) (x : ℝ) (hx : -1 ≤ x) : 1 + (n : ℝ) * x ≤ (1 + x) ^ n",
